As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 7,430 people and 2,717 households residing in the CDP. The racial makeup of the CDP was 88.3% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 6.4% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], 0.6% [[Asian (U.S. Census)|Asian]], 0.3% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 4.4% from two or more races. [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanic]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latino]] of any race were 4.7% of the population.

In the CDP, the population was spread out, with 14.7% under the age of 18, 4.3% under the age of five, and 24.1% who were 65 years of age or older.

The median income for a household in the CDP was $112,464, while the [[per capita income]] for the CDP was $54,058. About 6.3% of the population were below the [[poverty line]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/oakdalecdpnewyork|title=QuickFacts, Oakdale CDP, New York|accessdate=March 13, 2022|website=census.gov}}</ref>

